direct_enhancements.reason: Both methods involve comparing objects, but 'compare' is for ordering and 'equals' is for equality.
Both methods involve processing objects and generating a result, though for different purposes (ordering vs. hash code generation).
The 'compare' method relies on the 'apply' method of the Transformer to transform input objects before comparison.
The 'compare' method in TransformingComparator delegates the actual comparison to the 'compare' method of the decorated Comparator.
